task.summary: DiffEquation solver now knows Complex numbers. Matrix does not (yet? needed?). Complex eigenvalues lead to complex functions, sin and cos etc. work flawlessly.

Whole library now on Steroids, a.k.a. Complex values. Moved from JAMA to JAMpack. DiffEquation now knows everything, i.e. algebraic and geometric multiplicities are accounted for, complex eigenvalues are no problem, and data points other than 0 are also implemented.
Maybe at a later time I might include a method that will allow different points in time for all the differentiations, i.e. a vector t instead of just a Double.

Inhomogeneities working, which means diff equation solver is done. Now able to: - correctly do SVD (using JAMA algorithm) - find general and specialized solutions to differential equations or ODE systems - find solutions for homogeneous and inhomogeneous systems, with constant, polynomial, and exponential inhomogeneities
The only thing left to figure out is what to do with the cases that the sylvester equation can't solve. My guess is that theoretical work will conclude that the eigenvalues in the differential matrices can't ever appear in circuit systems, or the system is not solvable or something.

MNA works so far, it's missing output. Differential equations are being solved, voltage inputs work correctly now using an inner resistance.
SVD has been corrected; the implementation file has been replaced by the JAMA algorithm.
Need to implement - current sources (with inner resistance) - MNA output (substitute the matrix back into the DAE) - Ground current sourcing/sinking, possibly merge ground nodes into one - no ground current?
Could implement - dynamic inner resistance of voltage sources - mix polynomial with exponential inputs - data point vectors with different times

MNA almost complete.
Current source implemented (not tested yet). Ground connections made (not tested yet).
Changes undone from last time: no more inner resistance. Application should either throw an error or try to rectify by including a resistor.
Could implement - mix polynomial with exponential inputs - data point vectors with different times

MNA now complete, including u_C transformations to solve any system. Rudimentary graphing and circuit illustration application.
Could implement - mix polynomial with exponential inputs - data point vectors with different times
Basic graphing application (example package). Linear example working, with auto-adjusting graph, plot enabling and disabling buttons, and of course a circuit illustrator.
Drawing diodes, replacing them with resistors (either very large or 0)
Diodes working now. Regular switches are a pain. Not sure if I'll include.
one test didn't work anymore, i added a test configuration that shows a diverging circuit, oh and IDEAL DIODES BITCH. Rectifier now awesome.
